1122
01:26:42,105 --> 01:26:45,768
Target in sight!
Where in hell is Major Kong?

1123
01:27:09,532 --> 01:27:10,794
What about Major Kong?

1124
01:27:38,995 --> 01:27:42,692
Mr.President, I would not
rule out the chance...

1125
01:27:42,765 --> 01:27:45,825
to preserve a nucleus
of human specimens.

1126
01:27:45,902 --> 01:27:48,803
It would be quite easy...

1127
01:27:51,207 --> 01:27:56,304
at the bottom of some
of our deeper mine shafts.

1128
01:27:56,379 --> 01:28:01,214
The radioactivity would never penetrate
a mine some thousands of feet deep.

1129
01:28:01,284 --> 01:28:05,550
And in a matter of weeks, sufficient
improvements in dwelling space...

1130
01:28:05,621 --> 01:28:07,555
could easily be provided.

1131
01:28:07,623 --> 01:28:10,387
How long would you have
to stay down there?

1132
01:28:10,459 --> 01:28:14,327
Well, that's, you know--

1133
01:28:14,397 --> 01:28:17,059
Cobalt thorium G.

1134
01:28:27,310 --> 01:28:31,144
Radioactive half-life of--

1135
01:28:33,216 --> 01:28:37,949
I would think that possibly
one hundred years.

1136
01:28:40,289 --> 01:28:44,282
You mean, people could actually
stay down there for 100 years?

1137
01:28:44,360 --> 01:28:46,590
It would not be difficult,
Mein Fuhrer.

1138
01:28:46,662 --> 01:28:48,892
Nuclear reactors could--

1139
01:28:48,965 --> 01:28:51,331
I'm sorry, Mr.President.

1140
01:28:51,400 --> 01:28:55,200
Nuclear reactors could provide
power almost indefinitely.

1141
01:28:55,271 --> 01:28:58,104
Greenhouses could maintain
plant life.

1142
01:28:58,174 --> 01:29:01,769
Animals could be bred
and slaughtered.

1143
01:29:01,844 --> 01:29:06,281
A quick survey would have to be made of
the available mine sites in the country.

1144
01:29:06,349 --> 01:29:10,149
But I would guess
that a dwelling space...

1145
01:29:10,219 --> 01:29:13,882
for several hundred thousand of
our people could easily be provided.

1146
01:29:13,956 --> 01:29:17,084
Well, I would hate
to have to decide...

1147
01:29:17,159 --> 01:29:20,060
who stays up and who goes down.

1148
01:29:20,129 --> 01:29:24,031
Well, that would not be
necessary, Mr.President.

1149
01:29:24,100 --> 01:29:26,967
It could easily be accomplished
with a computer.

1150
01:29:27,036 --> 01:29:29,334
And the computer could
be set and programmed...

1151
01:29:29,405 --> 01:29:32,465
to accept factors
from youth, health...

1152
01:29:32,541 --> 01:29:35,704
sexual fertility, intelligence...

1153
01:29:35,778 --> 01:29:38,269
and a cross-section
of necessary skills.

1154
01:29:38,347 --> 01:29:40,611
Of course, it would be
absolutely vital...

1155
01:29:40,683 --> 01:29:44,642
that our top government
and military men be included...

1156
01:29:44,720 --> 01:29:49,555
to foster and impart the required
principles of leadership and tradition.

1157
01:29:55,598 --> 01:29:58,533
Naturally, they would breed
prodigiously.

1158
01:29:58,601 --> 01:30:01,399
There would be much time
and little to do.

1159
01:30:03,005 --> 01:30:07,942
But with the proper breeding techniques
and a ratio of, say...

1160
01:30:08,010 --> 01:30:10,774
ten females to each male...

1161
01:30:10,846 --> 01:30:15,476
they could then work their way back
to the present gross national product...

1162
01:30:15,551 --> 01:30:17,314
within 20 years.

1163
01:30:18,521 --> 01:30:21,251
But look, Doctor.
Wouldn't this nucleus of survivors...

1164
01:30:21,324 --> 01:30:26,421
be so grief-stricken
and anguished that they...

1165
01:30:26,495 --> 01:30:29,987
well, envy the dead
and not want to go on living?

1166
01:30:30,066 --> 01:30:32,899
No, sir. Excuse me.

1167
01:30:42,178 --> 01:30:46,114
When they go down into the mine,
everyone would still be alive.

1168
01:30:46,182 --> 01:30:48,275
There would be
no shocking memories...

1169
01:30:48,351 --> 01:30:53,015
and the prevailing emotion will be one
of nostalgia for those left behind...

1170
01:30:53,089 --> 01:30:55,956
combined with a spirt of...

1171
01:30:56,025 --> 01:30:58,459
bold curiosity for
the adventure ahead!

1172
01:31:15,978 --> 01:31:17,912
Doctor...

1173
01:31:20,116 --> 01:31:25,554
you mentioned the ratio
of ten women to each man.

1174
01:31:25,621 --> 01:31:28,749
Now, wouldn't that
necessitate the abandonment...

1175
01:31:28,824 --> 01:31:32,624
of the so-called
monogamous sexual relationship?

1176
01:31:32,695 --> 01:31:36,324
I mean, as far as men were concerned?

1177
01:31:36,399 --> 01:31:37,764
Regrettably, yes.

1178
01:31:37,833 --> 01:31:43,203
But it is a sacrifice required
for the future of the human race.

1179
01:31:43,272 --> 01:31:48,266
I hasten to add that since each man
will be required to do prodigious...

1180
01:31:50,046 --> 01:31:51,980
service along these lines...

1181
01:31:52,048 --> 01:31:55,848
the women will have to be selected
for their sexual characteristics...

1182
01:31:55,918 --> 01:31:59,684
which will have to be of
a highly stimulating nature.

1183
01:31:59,755 --> 01:32:03,589
I must confess, you have an
astonishingly good idea there, Doctor.

1184
01:32:04,760 --> 01:32:06,193
Thank you, sir.

1185
01:32:06,262 --> 01:32:09,231
We ought to look at this
from the military point of view.

1186
01:32:09,298 --> 01:32:13,234
I mean,
supposing the Ruskies...

1187
01:32:13,302 --> 01:32:16,237
stashed away some big bombs,
see, and we didn't?

1188
01:32:16,305 --> 01:32:19,206
When they come out in 100 years,
they could take over!

1189
01:32:19,275 --> 01:32:21,038
I agree, Mr.President.

